wiki.content: “TWIN TRIM” serves as the 24th track on Playboi Carti’s third studio album, MUSIC. This track pretty much acts like an interlude in the album, where Uzi does his typical flexing about money, talks about drugs, and focuses on mentioning some of the relationships he has with sum girls. While the participation of Lil Uzi Vert was rumored, Playboi Carti would confirm it even hours before the album or tracklist release by messaging Kai Cenat on Instagram about the album’s delay, including a personal message that said “YO BOY UZI SNAPPED” due to the friendship between Kai Cenat and Lil Uzi Vert. Hours before the album dropped, there were rumors about an interlude and a track with Lil Uzi Vert being on it, with some people also claiming that the song (later “JUMPIN”), is from the Pink Tape era, however, it is known that “TWIN TRIM” does not belong to this era.
